Former Big Brother Naija Lockdown housemate, Tochi has reinforced the popular notion that there’s dignity in labour. The reality TV star, in a tweet, explained the little sum earned by a person after due labour is more dignifying than given a large sum one hasn’t earned in any way. “10k that you worked hard for is actually better than 5million that’s given to you for free,” Tochi tweeted. The 29-year-old realtor has continued to receive knocks from users of Twitter. @Archy_Woman tweeted: “Let today be the last day you go drop motivational speeches.” @me_thegoodman said: “Una go just wake up de post nonsense everywhere Dem suppose seize your phone, flog you wire ontop.” @elkhelzta007 wrote: “No be him fault, I blame MTN wey dey give 10mb for 100 recharge.”   I’ve been performing for over 50 years – KI De…     N20m business startup: Davido carpets critic over proposal     I lose my manners when eating chicken – Rudeboy   @Tifeh_Adunni stated: “Somebody should collect the phone from this guy. Ko ye wi kotokoto.” @justplacid tweeted: “Oga stop this nonsense before dem go insulted you … you Dey 9ja Dey copy and paste meaningless motivational post, if it’s about staying relevant then go talk about how nothing is working in the country like the rest of other Twitter verified handles like yourself.” @ceo_graphs said: “Let today be the last day you motivate anybody.” @sonofomenuko asked: “How did you come up with this, please?” @w3bh4ck wrote: “You dey crase… nonsense guy, na wetin make that girl reject your proposal.” @a_rdavey stated: “This is a new sort kind of capitalism apologia No matter how hard you work, there are people earning 5 million practically for free.” @victorcudobi tweeted: “Tochi always tweeting rubbish with confidence no wonder Instagram no gree verify your account.” @Ogbogu_jeremiah asked: “Tochi how much did big brother give you? Did you work hard for it?”